de.hu.gralog.algorithm.result
Class AlgorithmResultContentTreeNode

java.lang.Object
  de.hu.gralog.algorithm.result.AlgorithmResultContent
      de.hu.gralog.algorithm.result.AlgorithmResultContentTreeNode

public class AlgorithmResultContentTreeNode
extends AlgorithmResultContent

This class extends AlgorithmResultContent in order to form a tree of contents. This class assumes that the whole tree is build by the algorithm. If you want a lazy implementation of the tree, i.e. the children are only calculated when the user decides to see them, you have to override this class. Special care has to be taken for the implementation of getAllStructures() - see the description of this method.

Author:
ordyniak

getAllStructures

protected Set<Structure> getAllStructures()
                                   throws UserException
This method returns all structures associated with the subtree rooted at this node. Note that this method is called by GrALoG before displaying the actual content. If you do want a lazy implementation of your tree you have to override this method.

Throws:
UserException
